      },
      "date": "2013-03-26 04:20:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Alex,\n\ncommit 6a65619 (LU-1581 mount: kernel do not parse ldd) and commit 31db8f9  prohibit passing LDD_F_UPDATE down to kernel, what is the initial purpose of them, is it that we should use 'lctl conf_param' to set failnode param instead of though mount options?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b248788af0f32ef88c9439fb297dba3260abcbb2",
